%20she%20was%20advised%20to%20eat%20only%201%2C200%20calories%20a%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKelsi%20Nagai%2C%20who%20is%20originally%20from%20the%20state%20of%20Washington%2C%20has%20been%20living%20in%20Japan%20for%20seven%20years.%20She%20has%20a%204-month-old%20son%2C%20who%20was%20born%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkindred-space-la-birth-clinic-people-color-maternal-mortality-rates-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emidwifery%20clinic%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20clinic%20closely%20monitored%20her%20weight%20during%20her%20pregnancy.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20advised%20to%20eat%20only%201%2C200%20calories%20a%20day%20in%20the%20third%20trimester%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20doctors%20%26quot%3Ballocated%26quot%3B%20her%2011%20kilograms%2C%20or%20just%20over%2024%20pounds%2C%20of%20weight%20gain%3B%20she%20gained%2013%20kilograms%2C%20or%20just%20under%2029%20pounds.%20The%20circumference%20of%20her%20belly%20was%20measured%20frequently%2C%20and%20the%20midwife%20also%20told%20her%20that%20she%20should%20be%20doing%20100%20squats%20a%20day.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20really%20intense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Watanabe%2C%20a%20mother%20from%20California%2C%20lives%20in%20central%20Tokyo%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20three-year-old%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWatanabe%20said%20her%20experience%20with%20motherhood%20in%20Japan%20had%20generally%20been%20positive.%20She%20concurred%20that%2C%20in%20her%20experience%20and%20from%20what%20she'd%20heard%20from%20others%2C%20obstetricians%20in%20Japan%20seemed%20fixated%20on%20weight%20gain%20during%20pregnancy%20and%20also%20tended%20to%20evaluate%20foreign%20patients%20according%20to%20charts%20calibrated%20for%20Japanese%20body%20types.%20But%20she%20managed%20to%20find%20a%20clinic%20%26quot%3Baccustomed%20to%20non-Japanese%20with%20different%20weights%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20where%20she%20was%20not%20scolded%20about%20her%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20mom%20said%20she%20was%20judged%20for%20working%20while%20her%20husband%20stayed%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENagai%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20was%20raised%20by%20a%20single%20father%2C%20decided%20he%20would%20take%20time%20off%20from%20work%20as%20a%20public-school%20teacher.%20Although%20the%20Japanese%20government%20offers%20generous%20paternity%20leave%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20Nagai's%20husband%20is%20entitled%20to%20receive%2085%25%20of%20his%20salary%20for%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20few%20new%20fathers%20take%20advantage%20of%20them.%20In%20Japan%2C%20mothers%20are%20still%20expected%20to%20take%20care%20of%20their%20children%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirteen%20weeks%20after%20giving%20birth%2C%20Nagai%20resumed%20work%20at%20an%20international%20school%20in%20Osaka%2C%20which%20is%20only%20in%20session%20180%20days%20a%20year.%20%26quot%3BIt%20made%20sense%20financially%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20was%20so%20much%20judgment%20that%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work.%20Japanese%20people%20tend%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdad-living-in-tokyo-shares-differences-in-school-culture-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehusband%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20as%20capable%20of%20taking%20care%20of%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn-laws%20don't%20often%20want%20to%20babysit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20American%20mothers%20also%20said%20that%20the%20concept%20of%20parents%20getting%20away%20from%20their%20children%20for%20an%20evening%20wasn't%20common%20in%20Japan%20and%20that%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20find%20a%20babysitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20American%20friends%20don't%20understand%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Christine%20Takisawa%2C%20a%20Michigan%20native%20who's%20the%20mother%20of%20a%205-year-old%20boy.%20%26quot%3B