%2Fa%3E%20worsens%2C%20some%20see%20fusion%20as%20the%20ticket%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelion-energy-fusion-company-backed-by-sam-altman-and-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabundant%2C%20fossil-fuel-free%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20critics%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Ffusion-nuclear-john-kerry-cop28-climate-power-energy-40ffa257eae528163f68554368cacfee%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20technology%20is%20too%20far%20behind%20to%20make%20a%20meaningful%20impact%20on%20the%20problem%20in%20the%20next%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Zap%20Energy%20hopes%20to%20have%20a%20pilot%20plant%20running%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20though%20it%20doesn't%20have%20a%20firm%20date%20for%20the%20goal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BZap%20Energy%20is%20still%20doing%20some%20fundamental%20R%20and%20D%2C%26quot%3B%20Ben%20Levitt%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20company's%20research%20and%20development%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20during%20a%20recent%20visit%20to%20the%20company%20offices.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20kind%20of%20building%20the%20plane%20as%20we%20fly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20fusion%20race%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222135%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20glass%20door%20with%20the%20words%20Zap%20Energy%20on%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65710b9a7a3c8094d5da7bc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZap%20Energy's%20offices%20are%20unassuming.%3Cp%3EJenny%20McGrath%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20just%20one%20of%20a%20handful%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-helion-energy-nuclear-fusion-power-plant-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efusion%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Northwest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocated%20not%20far%20from%20Zap%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20another%20startup%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelion-energy-fusion-company-backed-by-sam-altman-and-microsoft-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHelion%20Energy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fa-futuristic-plan-to-make-steel-with-nuclear-fusion-2a18ac35%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraised%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20%24600%20million%20in%20funding.%20It%20recently%20signed%20a%20deal%20to%20provide%20Microsoft%20with%20fusion%20power%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20US%20government%20and%20private%20backers%20are%20heavily%20invested%20in%20the%20future%20that%20fusion%20could%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20%246%20billion%20from%20private%20funders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fusionindustryassociation.org%2Ffusion-industry-reports%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehas%20poured%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20fusion%20research%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20including%20from%20the%20Bill%20Gates-backed%20Breakthrough%20Energy%20Ventures.%20Gates'%20investment%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zapenergy.com%2Fnews%2Ffirst-plasmas-fuzeq-series-c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtributed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Zap's%20%24160-million%20Series%20C%20funding%20round%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20what%20startup%20you're%20talking%20about%2C%20they're%20all%20racing%20to%20achieve%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20to%20create%20a%20fusion%20reactor%20that%20can%20generate%20more%20energy%20than%20the%20energy%20it%20takes%20to%20power%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20straightforward%20enough%20but%20scientists%20have%20only%20achieved%20such%20a%20feat%20twice%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eafter%20more%20than%2070%20years%20of%20trying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20fusion%20startup%20has%20a%20vision%20of%20how%20best%20to%20generate%20net%20fusion%20energy.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EZap%20Energy's%20version%20improves%20on%20a%20decades-old%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Z-pinch%20reactor%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225591%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%20metal%20machine%20with%20a%20long%20tube%20in%20front%20with%20circular%20protrusions%20coming%20off%20of%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65710bff7a3c8094d5da7bcb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223622%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20pinch%20portion%20of%20the%20Z-pinch%20device%20is%20what%20stabilizes%20the%20plasma%20so%20it%20can%20produce%20fusion%20reactions.%3Cp%3EJenny%20McGrath%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EZap%20calls%20its%20Z-pinch%20device%20FuZE%2C%20short%20for%20Fusion%20Z-Pinch%20Experiment.%20It's%20a%20long%20tube%20and%20has%20a%20simpler%20design%20than%20some%20of%20its%20competitors'%20devices%2C%20like%20Helion's%20magneto-inertial%20fusion%20technology%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BZ-pinch%20was%20the%20first%20concept%20that%20was%20studied%20for%20confining%20a%20plasma%20to%20attempt%20to%20get%20to%20fusion%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20also%20the%20first%20configuration%20that%20any%20grad%20student%20learns%20because%20it's%20the%20simplest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20work%2C%20gas%20puffs%20into%20the%20machine.%20A%20large%20burst%20of%20electricity%20turns%20the%20gas%20into%20a%20plasma.%20Then%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ean%20electrode%20creates%20a%20magnetic%20force%20that%20contains%20the%20plasma%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlasma%20is%20a%20state%20of%20matter%20found%20in%20stars%2C%20and%20it's%20within%20that%20plasma%20that%20the%20conditions%20for%20nuclear%20fusion%20occur%20%E2%80%94%20where%20atomic%20nuclei%20fuse%20and%20release%20massive%20amounts%20of%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221734%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20Zap%20Energy's%20Z-pinch%20device%20and%20how%20it%20generates%20plasma.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65832d51cefc010bea25ac4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20illustration%20of%20Zap%20Energy's%20Z-pinch%20experiment%20shows%20how%20the%20plasma%20is%20channeled%20into%20a%20beam%20that's%20then%20contained%20with%20magnets.%3Cp%3EZap%20Energy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20achieve%20this%20feat%2C%20the%20plasma%20needs%20to%20stay%20hot%20and%20dense%20for%20long%20enough%20for%20those%20nuclei%20to%20fuse.%20The%20main%20issue%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsites.uw.edu%2Fzpinchlab%2Fz-pinch-attributes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einstabilities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20quickly%20form%20in%20the%20plasma%20that%20can%20put%20a%20damper%20on%20the%20fusion%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20these%20instabilities%2C%20many%20researchers%20turned%20away%20from%20Z-pinch%20devices%20in%20the%2020th%20century%20and%20toward%20other%20types%20of%20reactors%20like%20tokamaks.%20But%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20Uri%20Shumlak%2C%20the%20chief%20scientist%20and%20founder%20of%20Zap%20Energy%2C%20started%20looking%20at%20Z-pinch%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20a%20graduate%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%2C%20Shumlak%20thought%20getting%20the%20plasma%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farpa-e.energy.gov%2Ftechnologies%2Fprojects%2Felectrode-technology-development-sheared-flow-z-pinch-fusion-reactor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20layers%20at%20different%20speeds%20could%20help%20smooth%20out%20the%20instabilities%20allowing%20the%20plasma%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20right%20conditions%20for%20fusion%20to%20occur%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Elong%20enough%20to%20generate%20net%20energy%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20stabilization%20mechanism%20here%2C%20called%20sheared%20flow%20stabilization%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20really%20Zap%20Energy's%20secret%20sauce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20close%20is%20Zap%20Energy%20to%20fusion%20power%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222824%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20what%20Zap%20Energy's%20fusion%20core%20will%20look%20like.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65832ef71c5c7b8c9a0a76c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221586%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIllustration%20of%20what%20Zap%20Energy's%20fusion%20core%20may%20look%20like%2C%20with%20the%20Z-pinch%20device%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20it%20all.%3Cp%3EZap%20Energy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDecades%20after%20the%20early%20experiments%2C%20Zap%20Energy%20thinks%20it's%20single-digit%20years%20away%20from%20using%20fusion%20to%20generate%20electricity.%20But%20there%20are%20still%20many%20hurdles%20in%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20Levitt%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EZap%20Energy%20can%20run%20its%20machine%20about%20100%20times%20a%20day%2C%20which%20lets%20researchers%20tinker%20with%20different%20configurations%20of%20the%20Z-pinch%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20to%20the%20Z-pinch%20machine%20in%20Zap's%20warehouse%20are%20large%20power%20banks%20surrounded%20by%20a%20chain-link%20fence.%20They%20provide%20the%20energy%20to%20generate%20the%20plasma.%20A%20pulse%20of%20energy%20might%20generate%20a%20plasma%20that%20lasts%20for%20about%20100%20microseconds%20because%20any%20longer%20and%20it%20%26quot%3Bcan%20go%20unstable%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20yet%20to%20generate%20fusion%20reactions%20with%20its%20device%2C%20let%20alone%2C%20produce%20net%20energy%20from%20those%20reactions%20to%20power%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20we%20think%20we%20know%20how%20it's%20going%20to%20work%2C%20but%2C%20of%20course%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20prove%20it%20experimentally%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20cost%20of%20fusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20generate%20electricity%2C%20Zap%20Energy%20plans%20to%20use%20tritium%2C%20which%20is%20great%20for%20fusion%20but%20happens%20to%20be%20wildly%20expensive%20costing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%20%2430%2C000%20per%20gram%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Ffusion-power-may-run-fuel-even-gets-started%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAt%2520%252430%252C000%2520per%2520gram%252C%2520it%2527s%2Ccan%2520burn%2520like%2520the%2520Sun.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZap%20Energy%20hasn't%20started%20working%20with%20tritium%2C%20yet.%20And%20while%20it%20can't%20control%20the%20cost%20of%20tritium%2C%20it%20can%20help%20keep%20costs%20down%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20its%20method%20to%20confine%20and%20control%20the%20plasma%20long%20enough%20for%20fusion%20is%20with%20a%20self-generated%20magnetic%20field.%20It%20uses%20a%20magnetically%20generated%20bottle%20where%20the%20reactor%20generates%20its%20own%20magnetic%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20not%20really%20imposing%20any%20kind%20of%20electromagnetic%20bottle%20around%20the%20plasma%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20that%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20the%20device%20doesn't%20rely%20on%20expensive%20super-conducting%20magnets%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Japan's%20new%20reactor%20that%20cost%20%24600%20million%20to%20build%20%E2%80%94%20to%20contain%20the%20plasma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGoing%20beyond%20break-even%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20first%20milestone%20for%20any%20fusion%20startup%20will%20be%20to%20reach%20scientific%20break-even%2C%20where%20you%20get%20as%20much%20energy%20from%20fusion%20as%20you%20use%20to%20power%20the%20plasma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20the%20ultimate%20goal%20is%20going%20beyond%20break-even%2C%20generating%2010%20to%2020%20times%20the%20amount%20of%20net%20energy.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20to%20get%20to%20another%20factor%20of%2010%20in%20gain%20there%2C%20and%20then%20you%20need%20to%20do%20it%20repetitively%2C%26quot%3B%20Levitt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20will%20require%20other%20engineering%20work%20that%20Zap%20said%20it's%20working%20on%20simultaneously%2C%20like%20creating%20capacitors%20that%20will%20create%20the%20Z-pinch%20over%20and%20over%20very%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20not%20and%20we%20will%20not%20hit%20break-even%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Zap%20Energy%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20yellow%20metal%20step%20ladder%20in%20front%20of%20a%20large%20cream-colored%20metal%20container%20next%20to%20a%20chain-link%20fence%20at%20Zap%20Energy's%20warehouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65710c7a58e7c0c29a2a7d87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZap%20Energy's%20power%20banks%20will%20be%20housed%20in%20containers%20like%20this%20one%20to%20make%20them%20more%20modular.%3Cp%3EJenny%20McGrath%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20Zap%20is%20working%20on%20creating%20its%20own%20power%20system%20that%20will%20charge%2C%20store%2C%20and%20discharge%20the%20necessary%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20these%20devices%20could%20surround%20the%20Z-pinch%20device%20in%20six%20to%20eight%20crates%20the%20size%20of%20shipping%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZap%20Energy%20is%20also%20exploring%20the%20possibility%20of%20taking%20over%20a%20portion%20of%20Washington%20State's%20only%20remaining%20coal%20power%20plant%2C%20which%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattletimes.com%2Fseattle-news%2Fenvironment%2Flewis-countys-centralia-bets-on-clean-energy-as-coal-economy-fades%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecease%20operations%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20plant%20will%20offer%20Zap%20space%20and%20grid%20connections%20that%20could%20help%20it%20one%20day%20generate%20200%20megawatts%20of%20electricity%20per%20hour%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eia.gov%2Ftools%2Ffaqs%2Ffaq.php%3Fid%3D104%26t%3D3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenough%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20power%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eia.gov%2Ftools%2Ffaqs%2Ffaq.php%3Fid%3D97%26t%3D3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earound%3C%2Fa%3E%20164%2C000%20homes%20if%20it%20operated%20continuously%3Cstrong%3E%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20the%20company's%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20setting%20up%20a%20plant%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Ryan%20Umstattd%2C%20the%20company's%20vice%20president%20of%20product%20and%20partnerships%2C%20said%20Zap's%20first%20customers%20will%20likely%20be%20early%20adopters.%20%26quot%3BIt%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20things%20like%20data%20centers%2C%20which%20are%20popping%20up%20all%20over%20the%20place%20and%20have%20significant%20demands%20for%20electricity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERegulating%20fusion%20power%20plants%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20there%20are%20no%20fusion%20energy%20plants%20in%20operation%2C%20the%20challenges%20and%20risks%20may%20not%20yet%20be%20fully%20understood%2C%20according%20to%20a%202020%20study%20from%20researchers%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0920379619308737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EImperial%20College%20London%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20Nuclear%20Regulatory%20Commission%20views%20fusion%20as%20safer%20than%20fission%20because%20it%20doesn't%20have%20the%20same%20risk%20of%20meltdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20NRC%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Fdocs%2FML2227%2FML22273A163.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evoted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20regulate%20nuclear%20fusion%20similarly%20to%20particle%20accelerators%20instead%20of%20like%20fission%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20make%20life%20easier%20for%20fusion%20companies%20like%20Zap%20because%20regulations%20for%20particle%20accelerators%20are%20%26quot%3Bfar%20simpler%2C%20less%20costly%2C%20and%20more%20efficient%20than%20the%20more%20complicated%20rules%20imposed%20on%20fission%20reactors%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeff%20Merrifield%2C%20a%20former%20NRC%20commissioner%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F04%2F20%2Fnuclear-fusion-will-not-be-regulated-the-same-way-nuclear-fission-is.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECNBC%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimpler%20doesn't%20mean%20simple%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20the%20US%20government%20pushing%20for%20a%20commercial%20fusion%20plant%20in%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20it%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fwhat-is-the-future-of-fusion-energy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etake%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20decades%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fnuclear-fusion-attracts-startupsand-skeptics-11636477774%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eto%20get%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20sizable%20chunk%20of%20the%20grid%20operating%20on%20fusion.%20And%20that's%20if%20all%20the%20technological%20and%20environmental%20issues%20are%20solved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzap-energy-fusion-power-plant-z-pinch-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703336881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65710d837a3c8094d5da7be6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzap-energy-fusion-power-plant-z-pinch-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Zap%20Energy%20is%20a%20startup%20that%20hopes%20to%20create%20a%20fusion%20power%20plant%20in%20less%20than%2010%20years.%20It%20plans%20to%20use%20a%20Z-pinch%20device%20to%20create%20fusion%20reactions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzap-energy-fusion-power-plant-z-pinch-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20mortgage%20rates%20to%20home%20sales%2C%20here%20are%20Fannie%20Mae's%20housing%20market%20forecasts%20for%20the%20next%202%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Housing%20market%20risk%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65807c7aa79e5746976a83f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222808%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBrianAJackson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFannie%20Mae%20outlined%20its%20housing%20market%20forecasts%20through%202025%2C%20including%20home%20sales%20and%20price%20growth.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELower%20borrowing%20costs%20will%20boost%20activity%2C%20but%20home%20sales%20will%20only%20marginally%20rise%20higher.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMortgage%20rates%20will%20average%206.7%25%20next%20year%2C%20close%20to%20levels%20seen%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20housing%20market%20will%20see%20some%20upside%20in%20the%20coming%20years%2C%20but%20persistent%20challenges%20will%20limit%20a%20bigger%20shift%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanniemae.com%2Fresearch-and-insights%2Fforecast%2Feconomic-developments-december-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Fannie%20Mae's%20latest%20forecast%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETotal%20home%20sales%20in%202024%20will%20come%20in%20at%20about%204.8%20million%2C%20largely%20flat%20compared%20to%20this%20year's%20expected%20level%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20jump%20to%205.4%20million%20in%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20drivers%20of%20slow%20sales%20are%20well%20known%20at%20this%20point%3A%20unaffordability%2C%20lock-in%20effects%2C%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20existing%20inventories%20freezing%20much%20of%20the%20housing%20market.%20While%20we%20believe%20these%20dynamics%20will%20slowly%20dissipate%20over%20time%2C%20they%20will%20remain%20obstacles%20in%202024%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20mortgage%20giant%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20existing%20home%20sales%20will%20undergo%20a%20slow%20recovery%20starting%20next%20year%2C%20after%20they%20hit%20a%20likely%20low%20point%20in%20October%2C%20at%20a%20seasonally%20adjusted%20annualized%20rate%20of%203.79%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20sales%20of%20new%20homes%20have%20also%20continued%20benefiting%20from%20the%20housing%20shortage%2C%20as%20well%20as%20builders'%20willingness%20to%20provide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-buydowns-are-helping-buyers-afford-homeownership-2023-2%5C%22%3Emortgage%20buydowns%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20trend%20continues%20into%20our%202024%20forecast%2C%20in%20which%20we%20expect%20new%20home%20sales%20to%20decline%20from%20current%20levels%20only%20slightly%20due%20to%20a%20modest%20economic%20contraction%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20shift%20in%20monetary%20policy%20has%20spurred%20a%20sharp%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafrica.businessinsider.com%2Fmarkets%2Fmortgage-rates-are-falling-at-the-fastest-pace-since-the-2008-housing-market-crash%2Ff7tvs33%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrop%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20quarter%2C%20Fannie%20Mae%20noted%20a%20limit%20to%20how%20far%20these%20rates%20will%20fall%3A%20it%20projects%20that%20the%2030-year%20fixed%20rate%20will%20average%206.7%25%20in%202024%2C%20before%20falling%20to%206.2%25%20in%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20down%20from%20the%20current%20level%20of%20just%20below%207%25%2C%20after%20they%20soared%20close%20to%208%25%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20recent%20pullback%20in%20mortgage%20rates%20to%206.95%25%20from%20their%20peak%20of%207.79%25%20in%20October%20points%20to%20an%20incoming%20rebound%20in%20sales%2C%20but%20even%20with%20recent%20declines%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20currently%20similar%20to%20those%20of%20the%20summer%20of%20this%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20price%20appreciation%20next%20year%20and%20growing%20refinancing%20activity%20should%20boost%20single-family%20mortgage%20originations%20from%20%241.5%20trillion%20to%20%241.9%20trillion%20in%202024%2C%20and%20to%20%242.3%20trillion%20in%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20although%20prices%20are%20set%20to%20keep%20growing%2C%20Fannie%20Mae%20doesn't%20expect%202023's%20momentum%20to%20carry%20over%20into%20the%20coming%20years.%20In%20its%20latest%20quarterly%20survey%20gathered%20in%20October%2C%20respondents%20saw%20home%20price%20growth%20reaching%202.4%25%20and%202.7%25%20in%202024%20and%202025%2C%20after%20surging%20an%20estimated%205.9%25%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20new%20construction%2C%20Fannie%20Mae%20noted%20that%20an%20economic%20slowdown%20is%20bound%20to%20rollover%20into%202024.%20But%20this%20should%20provide%20only%20a%20temporary%20setback%20to%20housing%20starts%2C%20as%20low%20interest%20rates%20will%20help%20single-family%20starts%20jump%20through%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultifamily%20starts%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20level%20off%2C%20however%2C%20given%20the%20inventory%20that's%20already%20hit%20the%20market%20and%20expectations%20of%20muted%20rent%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original