7a50edbc52a863c45d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20showing%20the%20chicken%20cooking%20in%20stock%20and%20vegetables.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Edmonds%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ray%2C%20start%20the%20recipe%20by%20adding%20all%20the%20ingredients%20needed%20for%20stock%20into%20a%20large%20pot%20and%20covering%20them%20with%20water.%20After%20bringing%20the%20pot%20to%20a%20boil%2C%20reduce%20the%20heat%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Blow%2C%20rolling%20boil%26quot%3B%20and%20cook%20for%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay%20suggested%20turning%20the%20chicken%20occasionally.%20I%20lost%20a%20bit%20of%20stock%20while%20trying%20to%20flip%20my%20bird%2C%20so%20I%20recommend%20using%20a%20large%20slotted%20spoon%20and%20some%20kitchen%20tongs%20to%20get%20the%20job%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPull%20apart%20the%20chicken%20and%20strain%20the%20stock.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rachael%20Ray's%20chicken%20noodle%20soup%20recipe%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6579d5c37a3c8094d5dc8831%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMake%20sure%20to%20keep%20debris%20out%20of%20the%20stock.%3Cp%3ELauren%20Edmonds%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20hour%2C%20remove%20the%20pot%20from%20the%20stove%20and%20let%20the%20stock%20cool%20until%20it's%20room%20temperature.%20Then%2C%20remove%20the%20chicken%2C%20place%20it%20on%20a%20separate%20surface%20like%20a%20baking%20sheet%2C%20and%20separate%20the%20meat%20from%20the%20skin%20and%20bones.%20Remember%20to%20pull%20the%20chicken%20into%20small%2C%20bite-sized%20pieces%20that%20won't%20be%20overwhelming%20in%20the%20soup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20stock%2C%20use%20a%20fine%20mesh%20sieve%20to%20strain%20it%20into%20a%20bowl%20carefully.%20Make%20sure%20there's%20no%20leftover%20debris%20