use%20they%20think%20they%20need%20to%20be%20wealthier%20first.%20It%20can%20also%20cause%20constant%20and%20undue%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKatz%20calls%20them%20%26quot%3Bmore%2C%20more%2C%20more%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoney%20dysmorphia%20can%20happen%20when%20you%20make%20'dangerous'%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20money%20dysmorphia%20impacts%20people%20of%20any%20generation%2C%20millennials%20today%20may%20feel%20it%20more%20than%20others.%20A%20survey%20last%20month%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-annual-income-price-of-happiness-wealth-retirement-generations-survey-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20think%20they%20need%20an%20annual%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%24525%2C000%20in%20order%20to%20be%20happy%20%E2%80%94%20four%20times%20as%20much%20as%20other%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdruckerwealth.com%2Fabout-us%2Fthe-dwm-squad%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGideon%20Drucker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20financial%20planner%20at%20Drucker%20Wealth%2C%20said%20this%20is%20something%20he%20sees%20with%20his%20clients%2C%20who%20are%20typically%20young%20families%20in%20their%2030s%20and%2040s%20who%20are%20making%20great%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20any%20objective%20measure%2C%20they're%20rich%2C%26quot%3B%20Drucker%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20they%20don't%20have%20that%20feeling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrucker%20said%20it's%20often%20folks%20who%20make%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%20amount%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20roughly%20%24250%2C000%20to%20%24750%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20depending%20on%20where%20you%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20making%20below%20that%20range%2C%20say%20%2475%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20you%20generally%20have%20to%20be%20very%20disciplined%20with%20how%20you%20spend%2C%20save%2C%20and%20budget.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20you're%20making%20%245%20million%20a%20year%2C%20you'll%20likely%20save%20enough%20for%20the%20future%20just%20by%20accident%20unless%20you%20go%20crazy%20with%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20the%20dangerous%20money%20range%20can%20generally%20afford%20everything%20they%20want%20and%20need%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%20However%2C%20they're%20not%20so%20wealthy%20that%20they%20can%20ignore%20planning%20for%20the%20future.%20%26quot%3BRetirement%20isn't%20going%20to%20take%20care%20of%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20Drucker%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20these%20people%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20feeling%20that%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20tends%20to%20stem%20from%20not%20having%20a%20clear%20view%20of%20their%20finances.%20Sometimes%2C%20after%20he%20starts%20working%20with%20a%20client%2C%20they%20realize%20they%20are%20better%20prepared%20and%20saving%20more%20money%20for%20the%20future%20than%20they%20thought%20they%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20at%20home%20managing%20finances.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6530361996f7540cd05fc590%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoney%20dysmorphia%20can%20happen%20when%20people%20don't%20have%20a%20good%20accounting%20of%20where%20they%20are%20at%20financially.%3Cp%3Ehobo_018%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20high-earners%20who%20report%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%2C%20Drucker%20said%20what%20he%20sees%20with%20his%20clients%20is%20that%20it's%20all%20relative%2C%20and%20they%20may%20be%20comparing%20themselves%20to%20how%20they%20think%20other%20wealthy%20people%20are%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20might%20mean%2C%20'I'm%20maxing%20out%20my%20401k.%20I'm%20sending%20my%20kids%20to%20private%20school.%20I%20have%20high%20property%20taxes.%20I'm%20putting%20money%20into%20my%20emergency%20reserves%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20explained%2C%20but%20added%20that%20they%20then%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20have%20as%20much%20money%20left%20over%20as%20they%20would%20like%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20financial%20anxiety%20is%20often%20not%20about%20the%20actual%20dollar%20amount%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20uncertainty.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20unknown%20that%20creates%20that%20anxiety%20more%20than%20the%20objective%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMap%20out%20what%20you%20have%2C%20what%20you%20need%2C%20and%20what%20you%20want%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKatz%20also%20said%20the%20first%20thing%20a%20person%20experiencing%20money%20dysmorphia%20or%20financial%20anxiety%20should%20do%20is%20take%20an%20honest%20accounting%20of%20their%20situation%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20how%20much%20they%20have%2C%20but%20also%20how%20much%20they%20need%20and%20how%20much%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20know%20the%20difference%20between%20what%20you%20need%20and%20what%20you%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20first%2C%20people%20should%20sit%20down%20and%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20is%20enough%20for%20them%2C%20and%20not%20just%20for%20the%20future%20and%20retirement%2C%20but%20as%20a%20current%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20recognize%20that%20the%20current%20number%20of%20what%20is%20%26quot%3Benough%26quot%3B%20will%20change%20over%20your%20life.%20%26quot%3BMap%20where%20you%20are%20now%2C%20and%20map%20your%20next%20stage%20of%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrucker%20agreed%20that%20planning%20can%20help%20people%20get%20over%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-plan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20rather%20than%20constantly%20comparing%20to%20others%20and%20wanting%20more%2C%20setting%20and%20meeting%20goals%20can%20help%20people%20feel%20confident%20they%20are%20making%20enough%20to%20provide%20for%20their%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20balancing%20current%20happiness%20with%20future%20needs%20and%20therefore%2C%20not%20saving%20too%20much%20%E2%80%94%20a%20problem%20that%20is%20impacting%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-henrys-401k-paycheck-to-paycheck-high-earners-millennials-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHENRYs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20high%20earners%2C%20not%20rich%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuccessful%20financial%20planning%20is%20not%20deferring%20all%20happiness%20and%20gratitude%20until%20you're%2075%20years%20old%20with%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20are%20living%20life%20to%20the%20fullest%2C%20you're%20enjoying%20day-to-day%20in%20a%20way%20that%20isn't%20detrimental%20to%20your%20future%20self%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-dysmorphia-why-wealthy-people-dont-feel-rich-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703335141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6580e938a79e5746976ac88f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-dysmorphia-why-wealthy-people-dont-feel-rich-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Money%20dysmorphia%20refers%20to%20when%20people%20have%20a%20distorted%20view%20of%20their%20finances%20that%20causes%20them%20to%20make%20poor%20personal%20and%20financial%20decisions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoney-dysmorphia-why-wealthy-people-dont-feel-rich-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pak%20Army%20Sets%20Own%20Post%20Ablaze%20To%20Aid%20Terrorist%20Infiltration%20Bid%20In%20Jammu%22