%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20envoy%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Riyad%20Mansour%2C%20called%20the%20resolution%20a%20%E2%80%9Cstep%20in%20the%20right%20direction.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMansour%20represents%20the%20Palestinian%20National%20Authority%2C%20which%20is%20based%20in%20Ramallah%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Foccupied-west-bank%2Ft-38397942%5C%22%3Eoccupied%20West%20Bank%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20is%20led%20by%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Toothless%E2%80%99%20resolution%3A%20Russian%20UN%20ambassador%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Vassily%20Nebenzia%2C%20has%20criticised%20a%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20on%20Gaza%20aid%20deliveries%20that%20was%20marked%20by%20compromises%20to%20avoid%20a%20US%20veto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Russia%2C%20which%20are%20permanent%20members%20of%20the%20Security%20Council%2C%20abstained%20from%20the%20vote%20but%20did%20not%20veto.%20Washington%20has%20vetoed%20previous%20resolutions%20calling%20for%20an%20immediate%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENebenzia%20called%20the%20resolution%20%E2%80%9Centirely%20toothless.%E2%80%9D%20Russia%20had%20supported%20the%20previous%20two%20motions%20with%20stronger%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20Washington%20of%20%E2%80%9Cshameful%2C%20cynical%20and%20irresponsible%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20and%20of%20using%20%E2%80%9Cgross%20pressure%2C%20blackmail%20and%20twisting%20arms%E2%80%9D%20to%20change%20the%20content%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20said%20the%20new%20resolution%20%E2%80%9Cwould%20essentially%20be%20giving%20the%20Israeli%20armed%20forces%20complete%20freedom%20of%20movement%20for%20the%20clearing%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Insufficient%2C%E2%80%