0a%20sensitive%20censor%20board.%20Twenty%20minutes%20shorter%20than%20its%20festival%20cut%2C%20the%20film%20follows%20a%20man%20(a%20very%20physical%20Manoj%20Bajpayee)%20from%20a%20tribal%20community%20in%20Jharkhand%2C%20whose%20land%20is%20usurped%20by%20a%20mining%20company%2C%20forcing%20him%20to%20join%20the%20Naxals%2C%20only%20to%20later%20flee%20to%20Mumbai%20where%20he%20works%20as%20a%20construction%20labourer.%20After%20being%20recognised%20by%20a%20local%20politician%20(Smita%20Tambe%2C%20who%20arguably%20had%20the%20highest%20impact%20to%20screen%20time%20ratio%20of%20the%20year)%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20orders%20the%20murder%20of%20his%20wife%20and%20implicates%20him%20for%20it%2C%20the%20man%20is%20forced%20to%20flee%20with%20his%20three-month-old%20baby%20tied%20to%20his%20back.%20Sparingly%20written%20and%20evocatively%20shot%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJoram%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20plays%20out%20like%20one%20of%20the%20most%20gruelling%20films%20of%20the%20year%20%E2%80%93%20where%20the%20marginalised%20find%20only%20injustice%20at%20various%20seemingly%20invisible%20junctures.%20Even%20after%20they%E2%80%99ve%20put%20their%20heads%20down%20and%20made%20peace%20with%20the%20oppression%20and%20injustice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fjoram-no-country-for-the-downtrodden-in-a-system-heavily-loaded-towards-the-rich-and-powerful%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Joram%E2%80%99%3A%20No%20Country%20for%20the%20Downtrodden%20in%20a%20System%20Heavily%20Loaded%20Towards%20the%20Rich%20and%20Powerful%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EThree%20of%20Us%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20happens%20when%20a%20selfless%2C%20domesticated%20(even%20while%20holding%20a%20full-time%20job)%20woman%20in%20an%20Indian%20family%20is%20forced%20to%20reckon%20with%20early-stage%20dementia%3F%20And%2C%20how%20do%20the%20people%20around%20her%20react%20when%20she%20suddenly%20starts%20putting%20her%20wishes%20ahead%20of%20everyone%20else%3F%20Avinash%20Arun%20Dhaware%E2%80%99s%20tenderly-written%20and%20excellently%20performed%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThree%20of%20Us%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20tries%20to%20explore%20this%20premise.%20Almost%20a%20companion%20piece%20to%20Celine%20Song%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPast%20Lives%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(2023)%2C%20Dhaware%E2%80%99s%20film%20delves%20into%20the%20what-ifs.%20Featuring%20spectacular%20turns%20by%20its%20four%20primary%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20Shefali%20Shah%2C%20Swanand%20Kirkire%2C%20Jaideep%20Ahlawat%20and%20Kadambari%20Kadam%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20impossible%20to%20not%20fall%20for%20the%20gentle%20ways%20of%20Dhaware%E2%80%99s%20film.%20Maybe%20going%20back%20to%20the%20beginning%2C%20as%20much%20as%20it%20refreshes%20old%20wounds%2C%20is%20the%20only%20form%20of%20catharsis%20some%20of%20us%20need.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EPokhar%20Ke%20Dunu%20Paar%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EParth%20Saurabh%E2%80%99s%20superbly%20observed%20and%20languorously-shot%20directorial%20debut%20follows%20the%20lives%20of%20two%20lovers%2C%20Sumit%20(Abhinav%20Jha)%20and%20Priyanka%20(Tanaya%20Khan%20Jha)%2C%20who%20elope%20from%20Darbhanga%20(Bihar)%20to%20Delhi%2C%20only%20to%20be%20hit%20by%20the%20pandemic.%20Forced%20to%20move%20back%20to%20their%20hometown%20and%20faced%20with%20the%20prospect%20of%20being%20confronted%20by%20vexed%20parents%20who%20have%20all%20but%20disowned%20them%2C%20the%20couple%20is%20forced%20to%20recalibrate%20their%20own%20bond%20while%20building%20their%20happily%20ever%20after.%20While%20Priyanka%20is%20grappling%20with%20what%20the%20future%20holds%20for%20the%20couple%2C%20Sumit%20is%20blissfully%20ignorant%2C%20not%20fully%20grasping%20that%20his%20days%20of%20wasted%20youth%20are%20over.%20Saurabh%E2%80%99s%20dialogues%20(Jha%20was%20credited%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98additional%20writer%E2%80%99)%20hardly%20feel%20written%2C%20and%20Pradeep%20Vignavelu%E2%80%99s%20camera%20seems%20to%20be%20eavesdropping%20on%20Sumit%2C%20Priyanka%2C%20and%20his%20friends.%20Saurabh%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20the%20rare%20%E2%80%98love%20story%E2%80%99%20where%20we%20see%20youthful%20vigour%20slowly%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20disappointments%20of%20adult%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EAfwaah%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20get%20a%20good%20price%2C%20I%20think%20I%E2%80%99ll%20even%20sell%20my%20other%20kidney.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20will%20you%20survive%20then%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CDoctors%20told%20me%20by%20then%20at%20least%20one%20of%20my%20kidneys%20will%20grow%20back!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20a%20darkly%20humorous%20conversation%20between%20a%20truck%20driver%20and%20a%20runaway%20henchman%20in%20Sudhir%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAfwaah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20world%2C%20gullible%20folk%20get%20their%20information%20via%20WhatsApp%20forwards%2C%20a%20news%20item%20about%20an%20on-the-run%20couple%20can%20suddenly%20take%20a%20communal%20turn%20by%20invoking%20%E2%80%98Love%20Jihad%E2%80%99.%20The%20privileged%20liberals%20can%20literally%20shut%20their%20doors%20to%20the%20needy%2C%20by%20simply%20closing%20their%20eyes%20and%20ears%20to%20the%20world%20burning%20around%20them.%20Sound%20familiar%3F%20Despite%20Nawazuddin%20Siddiqui%E2%80%99s%20affected%20performance%20as%20an%20urban%20adman%20whose%20F-bombs%20sound%20most%20unnatural%2C%20and%20the%20commentary%20being%20too%20on-the-nose%20in%20more%20than%20one%20place%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAfwaah%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20sees%20a%20reinvigorated%2C%20back-in-form%20Mishra.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20film%20sank%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%2C%20while%20Sudipto%20Sen%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Kerala%20Story%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20ran%20to%20packed%20theatres%2C%20is%20one%20stark%20circumstance%20about%20the%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%98topical%E2%80%99%20films%20Indian%20audiences%20find%20solace%20in%20these%20days.%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20to%20wager%20that%20it%20surely%20got%20a%20few%20despondent%20laughs%20from%20Mishra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fafwaah-film-review-mirror-india%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Afwaah%E2%80%99%20Holds%20an%20Important%20Mirror%20to%20Today%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EFaraaz%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20film%20on%20a%20terror%20attack%20that%20took%20place%20in%20Bangladesh%20in%202016%2C%20is%20arguably%20the%20most%20counter-intuitive%20film%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20young%20militants%20(led%20by%20Aditya%20Rawal%E2%80%99s%20Nibras)%20invoke%20Islam%2C%20kill%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Quran%2C%20say%20things%20like%20%E2%80%9CIslam%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekhatre%20mein%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20gloat%20about%20how%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejannat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20awaits%20them.%20On%20the%20surface%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFaraaz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20another%20hostage%20drama%20that%20villainises%20Muslims.%20However%2C%20Mehta%20and%20writers%20Raghav%20Kakkar%20and%20Kashyap%20Kapoor%20use%20the%20mould%20of%20a%20hostage%20film%20as%20a%20smokescreen%2C%20to%20meditate%20on%20religious%20dogma%20and%20fundamentalist%20beliefs.%20Tastefully%20shot%20by%20Pratham%20Mehta%20and%20with%20the%20momentum%20of%20a%20tense%20action%20film%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EFaraaz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reveals%20itself%20in%20its%20closing%20moments%20when%20it%20becomes%20a%20paean%20to%20the%20idealism%20of%20youth.%20In%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20film%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%20isn%E2%80%99t%20always%20visible%2C%20until%20they%20stand%20up%20for%20what%E2%80%99s%20right%20in%20one%20of%20the%20last%20scenes.%20Sublime%20touch!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Ffaraaz-hansal-mehta-review%5C%22%3EHansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Faraaz%E2%80%99%20Brings%20Nuance%20and%20Wit%20to%20its%20Display%20of%20Terror%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EGoldfish%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20might%20be%20a%20stretch%20to%20call%20Pushan%20Kripalani%E2%80%99s%20Goldfish%20a%20%E2%80%9CHindi%E2%80%9D%20film%20%E2%80%93%20given%20how%20it%E2%80%99s%20primarily%20set%20in%20London%2C%20and%20set%20around%20an%20Indian%20mother%20(Deepti%20Naval)%20and%20her%20half-British%20daughter%20(Kalki%20Koechlin)%2C%20who%20converse%20mostly%20in%20English.%20However%2C%20rarely%20has%20a%20dysfunctional%20parent-child%20bond%20been%20more%20accurately%20and%20frankly%20depicted%20on%20our%20screens.%20Koechlin%E2%80%99s%20character%20Anamika%20(referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98Mika%E2%80%99%20by%20her%20mother)%20is%20forced%20to%20move%20back%20home%2C%20after%20she%20learns%20her%20mother%20accidentally%20set%20the%20kitchen%20on%20fire%2C%20exhibiting%20early%20symptoms%20of%20dementia.%20Also%20compelled%20to%20reckon%20with%20her%20mother%E2%80%99s%20lover%2C%20a%20grocer%20down%20the%20street%20(Rajit%20Kapur)%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20named%20in%20her%20will%20to%20inherit%20the%20London%20home%20%E2%80%94%20Koechlin%E2%80%99s%20character%20is%20reckless%2C%20caring%2C%20kind%2C%20self-centred%2C%20all%20in%20the%20same%20breath.%20In%20a%20spectacular%20scene%2C%20she%20confides%20that%20only%20to%20irk%20her%20mother%2C%20she%20would%20go%20around%20telling%20people%20she%20was%20adopted.%20Naval%E2%80%99s%20character%20shoots%20back%20saying%20she%20would%20do%20the%20same.%20And%20both%20share%20an%20unexpected%2C%20hearty%20laugh.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20surprisingly%20moving%20scene%20of%20fractured%20bonds%2C%20with%20the%20undercurrent%20of%20repressed%20affection.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3ERocky%20Aur%20Rani%20Kii%20Prem%20Kahaani%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20all%20about%20questioning%20our%20parents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20could%20very%20well%20be%20the%20tagline%20of%20Karan%20Johar%E2%80%99s%202023%20film.%20Getting%20back%20to%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20chair%20after%20seven%20years%2C%20Johar%20takes%20the%20popular%20rom-com%20trope%20where%20a%20couple%20switch%20places%20and%20live%20with%20their%20partner%E2%80%99s%20family%2C%20and%20adds%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20personal%20flavour%20to%20it.%20This%20includes%20over-produced%20songs%2C%20ravishing%20costumes%2C%20painstaking%20production%20design%2C%20gargantuan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehaveli%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20with%20matriarchs%20barking%20orders.%20But%20underneath%20all%20the%20gloss%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20whiff%20of%20rebellion.%20It%20helps%20that%20both%20Ranveer%20Singh%20and%20Alia%20Bhatt%20%E2%80%93%20among%20the%20most%20gifted%20young%20actors%20working%20today%20%E2%80%93%20fully%20submit%20to%20Johar%E2%80%99s%20landscape%20and%20become%20shiny%20objects%2C%20but%20neither%20bereft%20of%20personality.%20The%20first%20half%20is%20arguably%20the%20funniest%20Johar%20has%20ever%20been.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Frocky-aur-rani-ki-prem-kahaani-karan-johar-ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-shabana%5C%22%3EIn%20%E2%80%98Rocky%20Aur%20Rani%20Ki%20Prem%20Kahaani%E2%80%99%2C%20Karan%20Johar%20Has%20His%20Tongue%20Firmly%20in%20His%20Cheek%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3E12th%20Fail%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVidhu%20Vinod%20Chopra%E2%80%99s%20film%20about%20a%20UPSC%20aspirant%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20surprising%2C%20satisfying%20Hindi%20films%20of%20the%20year.%20Based%20on%20a%20real-life%20account%20written%20in%20a%20book%20of%20the%20same%20name%20by%20Anurag%20Pathak%2C%20the%20film%20features%20the%20most%20sincere%20lead%20performances%20by%20Vikrant%20Massey%20and%20Medha%20Shanker.%20Sparingly%20using%20music%20to%20amp%20up%20the%20pathos%20through%20most%20of%20the%20film%2C%20Chopra%20earns%20the%20audience%E2%80%99s%20tears%20by%20being%20earnest%20and%20never%20succumbing%20to%20easy%2C%20dishonest%20tropes.%20The%20film%2C%20having%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20theatrical%20runs%20in%20recent%20history%20%E2%80%93%20being%20in%20theatres%20for%20more%20than%20three%20months%20in%20multiplexes%20%E2%80%93%20embodies%20the%20same%20striving%20spirit%20of%20its%20protagonist.%20What%20could%20be%20more%20poetic!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fvidhu-vinod-chopras-12th-fail-floors-you-with-its-kindness-and-sincerity%5C%22%3EVidhu%20Vinod%20Chopra%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9912th%20Fail%E2%80%99%20Floors%20You%20with%20its%20Kindness%20and%20Sincerity%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Cem%3ELust%20Stories%202%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Mirror%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKonkona%20Sen%20Sharma%E2%80%99s%20short%20in%20the%20Netflix%20anthology%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20Hindi%20films%20out%20there%20%E2%80%93%20for%20its%20economy%20and%20for%20featuring%20two%20of%20the%20most%20layered%20female%20characters%20written%20in%20recent%20memory.%20Isheeta%20(Tillotama%20Shome)%20is%20a%20single%20woman%20living%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20catches%20her%20maid%20Seema%20(Amruta%20Subhash)%20and%20husband%20Kamal%20(Shrikant%20Yadav)%20having%20sex%20in%20her%20bedroom.%20At%20first%20disgusted%20by%20the%20act%2C%20Isheeta%20becomes%20drawn%20to%20watching%20them%20have%20sex%2C%20while%20Seema%20%E2%80%93%20even%20after%20realising%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20being%20watched%20%E2%80%93%20embraces%20her%20own%20unspoken%20desires%20of%20exhibitionism.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20glorious%20premise%20executed%20with%20nifty%20precision%20by%20Sen%20Sharma%20and%20her%20team%20%E2%80%93%20managing%20to%20say%20more%20in%20its%2036-minute%20runtime%20than%20entire%20feature%20films.%20Apart%20from%20the%20star%20turns%20by%20Shome%2C%20Subhash%20and%20Yadav%20%E2%80%93%20Sagar%20Desai%E2%80%99s%20music%20is%20a%20highlight%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Mirror%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cb%3EPathaan%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESiddharth%20Anand%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20where%20it%20all%20began%20for%20Hindi%20cinema%20in%202023%20%E2%80%93%20with%20Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20playing%20the%20titular%20character%20of%20an%20R%26amp%3BAW%20spy%20teaming%20up%20with%20an%20ISI%20spy%20(Deepika%20Padukone)%20to%20take%20on%20a%20terrorist-for-the-highest-bidder%20(John%20Abraham).%20Even%20within%20its%20template%20of%20being%20an%20over-the-top%20action%20film%20%5Bshorthand%20for%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdon%E2%80%99t%20take%20it%20too%20seriously%E2%80%9D%5D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20film%20makes%20some%20subversive%20choices%3A%20having%20a%20protagonist%2C%20who%20was%20seemingly%20raised%20by%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edesh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(nation)%2C%20and%20saved%20from%20certain%20death%20by%20Afghan%20locals%3B%20having%20a%20terrorist%20%E2%80%93%20who%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20invoke%20Islam%20or%20Allah%20%E2%80%93%20while%20blowing%20a%20country%20up%3B%20showing%20a%20Pakistani%20character%20as%20an%20ally%2C%20also%20done%20in%20Salman%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ETiger%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20films.%20%3Cem%3EPathaan%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20nowhere%20near%20the%20best%20action%20film%20to%20have%20come%20out%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%20Anand%20seems%20capable%20of%20executing%20massive%20action%20set-pieces%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20saying%20something%20when%20one%20of%20the%20lasting%20images%20from%20the%20film%20is%20of%20the%20titular%20%E2%80%98hero%E2%80%99%20closing%20his%20ears%20as%20he%20witnesses%20the%20deaths%20of%20his%20colleagues%20(including%20Dimple%20Kapadia).%20It%20reclaims%20patriotism%20from%20the%20films%20that%20flippantly%20invoke%20the%20tricolour%20or%20the%20national%20anthem%20in%20the%20climax.%20That%E2%80%99s%20got%20to%20count%20for%20something.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fpathaan-movie-review%5C%22%3EWith%20Pathaan%2C%20Shahrukh%20Gives%20His%20Fans%20What%20They%E2%80%99ve%20Been%20Missing%20All%20These%20Years%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703316648000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22162650%2Ffilms-collage.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fbig-action-small-intimate-stories-subversion-best-hindi-films-2023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Just%20when%20the%20obituaries%20of%20Hindi%20cinema%20were%20being%20written%2C%20these%20ten%20show%20that%20it%20is%20premature%20to%20say%20that.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fbig-action-small-intimate-stories-subversion-best-hindi-films-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vin%20Diesel%20accused%20of%20sexual%20assault%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703316600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fs