%20Minister%2C%20dissuading%20the%20law%20students%20from%20taking%20up%20cases%20of%20people%20participating%20in%20%E2%80%98terrorist%E2%80%99%20activities%20is%20a%20dangerous%20proposition%2C%20not%20only%20undermining%20the%20two%20ministries%20he%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20but%20also%20fueling%20sentiments%20dangerous%20to%20the%20institutions%20that%20have%20been%20laboriously%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPresumption%20of%20guilt%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%E2%80%99s%20comment%20essentially%20tells%20the%20young%20law%20students%20to%20assume%20an%20accused%20as%20guilty%20and%20pass%20a%20moral%20judgment%20on%20an%20accused%20based%20on%20what%20he%20has%20been%20charged%20with%20by%20an%20investigating%20agency.%20Adjudicating%20somebody%20as%20guilty%20simply%20based%20on%20information%20collected%20by%20the%20investigating%20agency%20is%20in%20itself%20problematic.%20The%20assumption%20of%20guilt%20is%20also%20fundamentally%20at%20odds%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20criminal%20and%20constitutional%20law%2C%20which%20presumes%20innocence%20before%20convicting%20an%20individual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20statement%20also%20severely%20undermines%20the%20purpose%20of%20establishing%20the%20prominent%20National%20Law%20Universities%20in%20India%2C%20which%20were%20established%20in%20the%201980s%20to%20create%20specialised%20schools%20dealing%20with%20and%20engaging%20with%20the%20law%20and%20to%20create%20an%20excellent%20stream%20of%20lawyers%20who%20would%20serve%20the%20cause%20of%20justice%20and%20contribute%20to%20making%20the%20law%20accessible%20to%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689285%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Sora%20Shimazaki%2FPexels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20appears%20to%20seek%20to%20reverse%20that%20by%20training%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20young%20lawyers%20in%20India%20to%20believe%20everything%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20investigative%20agencies%20say.%20What%20is%20problematic%20is%20the%20argument%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20terrorism%2C%20we%20should%20all%20agree%20to%20disregard%20the%20guarantees%20of%20the%20constitution%20that%20entitle%20every%20accused%20to%20legal%20representation%20and%20a%20fair%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20claiming%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%98ethical%E2%80%99%20not%20to%20take%20on%20such%20cases%20because%20it%20%E2%80%98damages%E2%80%99%20the%20country%2C%20young%20lawyers%20are%20being%20asked%20to%20forsake%20their%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20duty%20to%20defend%20the%20accused.%20The%20statement%20of%20the%20minister%20essentially%20shows%20the%20impatience%20with%20due%20process%20of%20law%20and%20the%20increasing%20impunity%20afforded%20to%20those%20who%20claim%20themselves%20to%20be%20the%20custodians%20of%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncrease%20in%20the%20use%20of%20anti-terror%20laws%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20fundamentally%20incorrect%20here%20is%20the%20idea%20that%20all%20people%20charged%20with%20terrorism%20are%20%E2%80%98terrorists%E2%80%99.%20The%20desire%20to%20push%20this%20story%20stems%20from%20the%20current%20government%E2%80%99s%20desperation%2C%20as%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20terrorism%20cases%20brought%20against%20students%2C%20activists%2C%20and%20journalists%2C%20among%20others.%20One%20merely%20needs%20to%20look%20at%20the%20rise%20in%20anti-terror%20laws%20and%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA)%20cases%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NCRB%E2%80%99s%202022%20crime%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Findia%2Fncrb-data-shows-uapa-cases-increased-by-23-in-2022-while-those-under-sedition-down-by-nearly-75%2F1871719%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%2017.9%25%20increase%20in%20UAPA%2C%20with%20a%20total%20of%201%2C005%20cases%20documented%20across%20the%20country%20in%202022.%20This%20represents%20a%20significant%20increase%20from%202021%2C%20when%20814%20instances%20were%20reported%2C%20to%20796%20cases%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20very%20low%20number%20of%20convictions%20in%20these%20cases%20shows%20how%20unfairly%20and%20viciously%20people%20are%20punished%20in%20these%20cases%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20spend%20years%20in%20prison%20because%20bail%20is%20impossible%20to%20obtain.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20the%20botched-up%20investigation%20damages%20the%20crucial%20years%20of%20persons%20accused%20under%20these%20severe%20laws.%20According%20to%20data%20released%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fmonsoon-session-parliament-4690-people-arrested-under-uapa-from-2018-2020-only-149-convicted-government%23read-more%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20of%204%2C690%20people%20arrested%20between%202018%20and%202020%2C%20only%203%25%20were%20convicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20liberty%20of%20a%20citizen%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20and%20we%20need%20both%20a%20watchful%20judiciary%20providing%20a%20check%20and%20balance%20on%20the%20unrestricted%20powers%20of%20investigating%20agencies%20and%20fearless%20lawyers%20who%20represent%20the%20accused%20in%20court.%20Without%20both%2C%20democracy%20would%20fall%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20authoritarians%20eager%20to%20stifle%20due%20process.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20courts%20and%20law%20schools%20must%20not%20disregard%20the%20warning%20signs%20on%20the%20wall.%20It%20is%20even%20more%20critical%20today%20that%20law%20schools%20cultivate%20a%20%3Cem%3Etigerish%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebreed%20of%20young%20lawyers%20who%20are%20gutsy%20enough%20to%20fight%20the%20good%20fight%20on%20behalf%20of%20people%20wrongfully%20charged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20a%20practicing%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Delhi.%20She%20is%20also%20associated%20with%20the%20Human%20Rights%20Law%20Network%2C%20Delhi.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703251848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22171032%2FEffect-41.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-argue-cases-for-terror-accused-why-gujarat-ministers-advice-to-law-students-is-wrong%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Implicit%20in%20such%20a%20view%20is%20that%20all%20those%20charged%20with%20terrorism%20are%20'terrorists'%2C%20which%20is%20fundamentally%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20criminal%20law.%20Rushikesh%20Patel's%20remarks%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation's%20mindset%2C%20as%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20in%20terrorism%20cases.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdont-argue-cases-for-terror-accused-why-gujarat-ministers-advice-to-law-students-is-wrong%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We%20Were%20Created%20in%20Our%20Creator's%20Image%20%E2%80%93%20Mimicry%20Is%20Our%20Manifest%20Destiny%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22183055%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%2C%20as%20is%20said%2C%20imitation%20is%20the%20sincerest%20form%20of%20flattery%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20affronted%20by%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%20Kalyan%20Banerjee%20mimicking%20him%2C%20Vice-President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20should%20applaud%20the%20act%2C%20which%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20recorded%20on%20his%20cell%20phone%20and%20which%20has%20created%20a%20%3Cem%3Etoofan%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20teacup.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20mechanics%20of%20humour%20%E2%80%93%20if%20something%20as%20spontaneous%20and%20effervescent%20as%20humour%20can%20be%20associated%20with%20the%20prosaic%20nuts%20and%20bolts%20of%20mechanism%20%E2%80%93%20the%20target%20of%20humour%20must%20always%20be%20someone%20superior%20in%20power%2C%20pelf%2C%20or%20status%20than%20the%20humorist.%20Humour%20must%20be%20directed%20upwards%2C%20not%20downwards%3B%20at%20princes%2C%20not%20paupers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20it%20was%20for%20this%20subconscious%20reason%20that%20Nehru%20was%20seldom%20more%20pleased%20than%20when%20he%20was%20lampooned%20by%20cartoonists%20like%20Shankar%2C%20master%20of%20the%20graphic%20art%20of%20mimicry.%20By%20mimicking%20the%20V-P%2C%20the%20MP%20far%20from%20belittling%20him%2C%20was%20implicitly%20acknowledging%20the%20former%E2%80%99s%20eminence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20term%20mimic%2C%20as%20noun%20or%20verb%2C%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20Greek%20word%20for%20imitation%2C%20%E2%80%98mimesis%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20itself%20comes%20from%20%E2%80%98mimos%E2%80%99%2C%20imitator%20or%20actor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20ancient%20Greece%2C%20mimesis%20was%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20all%20art%2C%20from%20poetry%20and%20drama%20to%20sculpture.%20In%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ERepublic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Plato%20distinguishes%20between%20mimesis%20and%20diegesis%2C%20which%20is%20narration.%20Think%20of%20the%20two%2C%20one%20as%20a%20novel%2C%20a%20fictive%20imagination%20of%20events%2C%20and%20the%20other%20as%20a%20diary%2C%20a%20recording%20of%20real%20happenings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMimesis%20was%20central%20to%20Aristotle%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EPoetics%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20which%20imitation%20of%20nature%20and%20the%20natural%20world%20was%20the%20basis%20of%20all%20literary%20creativity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAristotle%20deemed%20literature%2C%20to%20which%20both%20tragedy%20and%20comedy%20belong%2C%20to%20be%20more%20educative%20than%20history%2C%20as%20history%20deals%20with%20specific%20facts%20while%20literature%20is%20at%20liberty%20to%20roam%20the%20imaginary%20and%20imaginative%20realm%20of%20what%20might%20have%20been%2C%20as%20an%20imitation%20or%20mimicry%20of%20restrictive%20reality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECommentators%20and%20interpreters%20of%20the%20mimetic%20include%20Samuel%20Taylor%20Coleridge%2C%20Sigmund%20Freud%2C%20Jacques%20Derrida%2C%20Iris%20Murdoch%2C%20and%20mythologist%20Roberto%20Calasso.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20%3Cem%3ETradition%20and%20the%20Individual%20Talent%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20T.S.%20Eliot%20said%20that%20all%20creative%20writers%2C%20consciously%20or%20otherwise%2C%20reflect%20and%20echo%2C%20or%20mimic%20if%20you%20like%2C%20those%20who%20have%20preceded%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Milton%20would%20not%20have%20been%20a%20Milton%20without%20a%20preceding%20Shakespeare%2C%20nor%20for%20that%20matter%2C%20a%20T.S.%20Eliot%20a%20T.S.%20Eliot%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEliot%20was%20delighted%20when%20a%20sharp-eyed%20reader%20charged%20him%20with%20copycatting%20the%20repeated%20refrain%20of%20%E2%80%9Cfalls%20the%20shadow%E2%80%9D%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hollow%20Men%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20from%20Ernest%20Dowson%E2%80%99s%20poem%2C%20%3Cem%3ECynara%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20about%20a%20lost%20love%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20fell%20thy%20shadow%2C%20Cynara!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFar%20from%20taking%20the%20reader%E2%80%99s%20comment%20as%20an%20accusation%20of%20plagiarism%2C%20or%20imitation%2C%20Eliot%20saw%20it%20as%20a%20vindication%20of%20his%20proposition%20of%20the%20passing%20on%20of%20the%20baton%20of%20literary%20tradition%20through%20successive%20inheritors%20of%20a%20common%20legacy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELess%20academically%2C%20but%20more%20amusingly%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20comic%20Tom%20Lehrer%20did%20his%20own%20take%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20imitation%20and%20mimicry%20when%20he%20sang%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CPlagiarise%2C%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%20do%20you%20think%20God%20gave%20you%20eyes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20to%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise%2C%20plagiarise!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMimicry%2C%20in%20myriad%20forms%2C%20is%20our%20manifest%20destiny.%20How%20could%20it%20not%20be%2C%20seeing%20that%20our%20Creator%2C%20in%20an%20act%20of%20self-mimicry%2C%20created%20us%20in%20His%20%E2%80%93%20or%20Her%20%E2%80%93%20own%20image%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJug%20Suraiya%20is%20a%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703250223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22183055%2FUntitled-design-10.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmimicry-jagdeep-dhankhar-kalyan-banerjee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Keep%20this%20grand%20act%20of%20self%20mimicry%20in%20mind%2C%20Vice-President%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20should%20applaud